b'' b'' b' too bad. in fact, by nazi armenians in europe had established' b' a vast network of pro-german collaborators, that extended over two' b' continents.' b'' b'before you go calling the kettle black, keep in mind that the' b'turkish government was a strong supporter of nazi germany and' b'played a vital role in supplying it with oil until the allies' b'invaded iran. complaining about armenian complicity with the' b'nazis does little good when turkey played a much bigger role.' b'' b"tell me, 'kmagnacca', were you high on 'arromdian of asala/sdpa/arf'" b'when you wrote that? humane behavior and tolerance of turks was a' b'legend even years ago when they accepted tens of thousands of' b'jews from spain who were fleeing from the spanish inquisition. again,' b"many jewish families escaping from nazi armenians and hitler's nazi" b"germany took refugee in turkiye during the 1940's. turkish people" b'have unselfishly given home, protection, and freedom to the jews over' b'the centuries, including to thousands and thousands of them during' b'the second world war. get a life or a cup of turkish coffee.' b'' b'"history of the jews in the islamic countries," chapters in parts i and ii,' b'jarusalem, zalman shazar center for jewish history, b'' b'baron, salo w., "a social and religious history of the jews," new york,' b'columbia university press, vols. iii, v, xviii.' b'' b'benardete, mair jose, "hispanic culture and character of the sephardic' b'jews," new york, sepher-hermon press, 2nd corrected edition, (original' b'publication b'' b'lewis, bernard, eds., "christians and jews in the ottoman empire," new york,' b'holmes meier, vol. i, the central lands.' b'' b'"la turquie dan les archives des grand orient de france: les loges b'in jean-louis bacque-graumont and paul dumont, eds., economie et societes' b"dans l'empire ottoman, paris, centre national de la reserche scientifique," b'1983.' b'' b'inalcik, halil, "turkish-jewish relations in the ottoman empire," b'' b'sevil